1.  Attempting to blind opponents.  This is effective only against morons anyone with hotkeyed spells can circumvent this.  It is also highly resisted, you are better off inflicting damage rather than wasting time doing this.<br>
<br>
2.  Rooting pets.  All too often I see people wasting precious time trying to root pets this time too would be better off being spent inflicting damage.  Pet roots are very difficult to get to take and never hold long,  in the meantime you are sucking up damage while not dishing it out and that = a loss.<br>
<br>
3.  Not healing enough.  If you are a class that can heal then you are a class that has twice the mana efficiency of the guy doing the nuking.  Incaster battles any healer can pretty much heal off an entire bar of a wizards mana so heal early and heal lots.<br>
<br>
4.  Running mouth syndrome.  Too many people talking about who is better at duels this class or that and not enough time spent duelling.  Bottom line is you get good at duels just like anything else by doing it and the more you do it the badder you will become.  There is no risk in duelling worst thing is you might get a bruised ego but you'll not lose any equipment or anything like that and if you do it right you won't ever lose exp either.  <br>
